to construct a feature of,

100
00:04:32,735 --> 00:04:35,375
say, the average
rating of this movie.

101
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:38,975
This feature again
depends on the ratings

102
00:04:38,975 --> 00:04:42,560
that users are given but again,

103
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,805
does nothing wrong with that.

104
00:04:43,805 --> 00:04:45,500
You can construct a feature for

105
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:47,360
a given movie that

106
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:50,090
depends on the ratings
that movie had received,

107
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,950
such as the average
rating of the movie.

108
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:54,065
Or if you wish,
you can also have

109
00:04:54,065 --> 00:04:56,960
average rating per country or

110
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:59,810
average rating per user
demographic as they

111
00:04:59,810 --> 00:05:01,280
want to construct other types of

112
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:03,095
features of the movies as well.

113
00:05:03,095 --> 00:05:05,405
With this, for each movie,

114
00:05:05,405 --> 00:05:07,580
you can then construct
a feature vector,

115
00:05:07,580 --> 00:05:10,450
which I'm going to
denote x subscript m,

116
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:12,125
m stands for movie,

117
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:14,795
and superscript i for movie i.

118
00:05:14,795 --> 00:05:16,430
Given features like this,

119
00:05:16,430 --> 00:05:20,530
the task is to try to
