160
00:07:30,235 --> 00:07:34,445
If v, u, that is a user vector,

161
00:07:34,445 --> 00:07:38,060
turns out to capture
the user's preferences,

162
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:40,125
say is 4.9,

163
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:42,375
0.1, and so on.

164
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:43,950
Lists of numbers like that.

165
00:07:43,950 --> 00:07:46,715
The first number captures

166
00:07:46,715 --> 00:07:49,085
how much do they
like romance movies.

167
00:07:49,085 --> 00:07:51,740
Then the second number
captures how much do they

168
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:54,590
